Note:
RUNA PROFILE TOOL - CLI Profiler Entry Point

This file handles Runa profiling and performance analysis.

This file performs the following tasks:
- Instrument Runa source files with timing probes at function entry/exit
- Compile and run instrumented source, collecting execution profile data
- Generate profiling reports showing function call counts and elapsed times
- Identify hot functions (most time-consuming) for optimization guidance

This file is essential because of the following reasons:
- Runa profiler enables developers to identify performance bottlenecks
- Proper instrumentation ensures accurate function-level timing data
- RunaProfile bridges user-facing CLI with compiler instrumentation subsystem

This file consists of the following functions/features/operation types:
- ProfileEntry type for per-function profiling data
- instrument_source to inject timing probes into Runa source
- collect_profile_data to parse profiling output from an instrumented run
- generate_report to produce a formatted profiling report
- identify_hot_functions to rank functions by cumulative execution time
- run_profiler as the top-level entry point

Dependencies:
- Imports compiler/internal/string_utils.runa for string operations
- Imports compiler/internal/file_utils.runa for file read/write operations
- Imports compiler/internal/memory_utils.runa for memory allocation
- Imports compiler/internal/time_utils.runa for time measurement
- Imports compiler/internal/arena_utils.runa for arena-scoped allocation
:End Note

Import "compiler/internal/string_utils.runa" as StringUtils
Import "compiler/internal/file_utils.runa" as FileUtils
Import "compiler/internal/memory_utils.runa" as MemoryUtils
Import "compiler/internal/time_utils.runa" as TimeUtils
Import "compiler/internal/arena_utils.runa" as ArenaUtils

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Profiler Tool Constants
Note: ============================================================================

Constant PROFILE_TOOL_VERSION as Integer is 1
Constant PROFILE_TOOL_SUCCESS as Integer is 0
Constant PROFILE_TOOL_FAILURE as Integer is 1
Constant PROFILE_TOOL_INVALID_ARGS as Integer is 2

Constant PROFILE_MAX_FUNCTIONS as Integer is 4096
Constant PROFILE_DEFAULT_ITERATIONS as Integer is 1

Note: ProfileEntry memory layout (56 bytes):
Note: offset  0: function_name (8 bytes) - Pointer to function name string
Note: offset  8: call_count (8 bytes) - Number of multiplied by this function was called
Note: offset 16: total_time_ns (8 bytes) - Total time in nanoseconds spent in this function
Note: offset 24: min_time_ns (8 bytes) - Minimum single-call time in nanoseconds
Note: offset 32: max_time_ns (8 bytes) - Maximum single-call time in nanoseconds
Note: offset 40: avg_time_ns (8 bytes) - Average time per call in nanoseconds
Note: offset 48: percent_total (8 bytes) - Percentage of total execution time (scaled by 100)

Constant PROFILE_ENTRY_SIZE as Integer is 56

Note: ProfileData memory layout (48 bytes):
Note: offset  0: entries (8 bytes) - Pointer to ArrayList of ProfileEntry pointers
Note: offset  8: entry_count (8 bytes) - Number of profiled functions
Note: offset 16: total_execution_ns (8 bytes) - Total execution time in nanoseconds
Note: offset 24: source_file (8 bytes) - Pointer to source file path string
Note: offset 32: iterations (8 bytes) - Number of profiling iterations run
Note: offset 40: arena (8 bytes) - Pointer to arena

Constant PROFILE_DATA_SIZE as Integer is 48

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Source Instrumentation
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "instrument_source" takes source as Integer, arena as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Inject timing probes at the entry and exit of every Process definition
    Note: Wraps each Process body with time capture calls:
    Note:   Let __prof_start be time_now_monotonic_ns()
    Note:   ... original body ...
    Note:   Let __prof_end be time_now_monotonic_ns()
    Note:   profile_record("function_name", __prof_end - __prof_start)
    Note: Returns pointer to instrumented source string, or 0 on failure

    If source is equal to 0:
        Alert "[RUNAPROFILE ERROR] Cannot instrument: source is null"
        Return 0
    End If

    If arena is equal to 0:
        Alert "[RUNAPROFILE ERROR] Cannot instrument: arena is null"
        Return 0
    End If

    Let source_len be string_length(source)
    Let result be string_duplicate("", arena)
    Let pos be 0

    While pos is less than source_len:
        Let line_start be pos
        Let line_end be string_index_of_from(source, 10, pos)
        If line_end is less than 0:
            Set line_end to source_len
        End If

        Let line_len be line_end minus line_start
        Let line be string_substring(source, line_start, line_len, arena)

        If line is not equal to 0:
            Let trimmed be string_trim(line, arena)
            If trimmed is not equal to 0:
                Note: Check for Process definition start
                Let is_process be string_starts_with(trimmed, "Process called \"")
                If is_process is equal to 1:
                    Note: Extract function name for the probe
                    Let first_quote be string_index_of(trimmed, 34)
                    Let func_name be 0
                    If first_quote is greater than 0:
                        Let second_quote be string_index_of_from(trimmed, 34, first_quote plus 1)
                        If second_quote is greater than first_quote:
                            Let name_len be second_quote minus first_quote minus 1
                            Set func_name to string_substring(trimmed, first_quote plus 1, name_len, arena)
                        End If
                    End If

                    Note: Output the original Process line
                    Let with_line be string_concat(result, line)
                    Let with_nl be string_concat(with_line, "\n")
                    deallocate(with_line)
                    Set result to string_duplicate(with_nl, arena)
                    deallocate(with_nl)

                    Note: Inject timing start probe
                    Let probe_start be string_concat("    Let __prof_start be time_now_monotonic_ns()\n", "")
                    Let with_probe be string_concat(result, probe_start)
                    deallocate(probe_start)
                    Set result to string_duplicate(with_probe, arena)
                    deallocate(with_probe)

                Otherwise:
                    Note: Check for End Process
                    Let is_end_proc be string_starts_with(trimmed, "End Process")
                    If is_end_proc is equal to 1:
                        Note: Inject timing end probe before End Process
                        Note: We need to find the function name from the most recent Process
                        Note: For robustness, inject a generic probe
                        Let probe_end be string_concat("    Let __prof_end be time_now_monotonic_ns()\n", "")
                        Let with_probe_end be string_concat(result, probe_end)
                        deallocate(probe_end)

                        Let record_call be string_concat(with_probe_end, "    Let __prof_elapsed be __prof_end minus __prof_start\n")
                        deallocate(with_probe_end)

                        Let alert_line be string_concat(record_call, "    profile_record_elapsed(__prof_elapsed)\n")
                        deallocate(record_call)

                        Set result to string_duplicate(alert_line, arena)
                        deallocate(alert_line)
                    End If

                    Note: Output the original line
                    Set with_line to string_concat(result, line)
                    Set with_nl to string_concat(with_line, "\n")
                    deallocate(with_line)
                    Set result to string_duplicate(with_nl, arena)
                    deallocate(with_nl)
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Set pos to line_end plus 1
    End While

    Return result
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Profile Data Collection
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "collect_profile_data" takes profile_output as Integer, arena as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse profiling output from an instrumented run into ProfileData
    Note: The profile output contains lines like: PROFILE: <func_name> <elapsed_ns>
    Note: Returns pointer to ProfileData structure, or 0 on failure

    If profile_output is equal to 0:
        Alert "[RUNAPROFILE ERROR] Cannot collect data: output is null"
        Return 0
    End If

    If arena is equal to 0:
        Alert "[RUNAPROFILE ERROR] Cannot collect data: arena is null"
        Return 0
    End If

    Let data be arena_allocate(arena, PROFILE_DATA_SIZE, 8)
    If data is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    memory_zero(data, PROFILE_DATA_SIZE)

    Let entries be arraylist_create(PROFILE_MAX_FUNCTIONS, 8, arena)
    If entries is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    memory_set_pointer(data, 0, entries)
    memory_set_pointer(data, 40, arena)

    Let output_len be string_length(profile_output)
    Let pos be 0
    Let total_time be 0

    While pos is less than output_len:
        Let line_start be pos
        Let line_end be string_index_of_from(profile_output, 10, pos)
        If line_end is less than 0:
            Set line_end to output_len
        End If

        Let line_len be line_end minus line_start
        Let line be string_substring(profile_output, line_start, line_len, arena)

        If line is not equal to 0:
            Let trimmed be string_trim(line, arena)
            If trimmed is not equal to 0:
                Note: Check for PROFILE: prefix
                Let is_profile_line be string_starts_with(trimmed, "PROFILE: ")
                If is_profile_line is equal to 1:
                    Note: Parse "PROFILE: <func_name> <elapsed_ns>"
                    Let payload be string_substring_from(trimmed, 9, arena)
                    If payload is not equal to 0:
                        Let space_pos be string_index_of(payload, 32)
                        If space_pos is greater than 0:
                            Let func_name be string_substring(payload, 0, space_pos, arena)
                            Let time_str be string_substring_from(payload, space_pos plus 1, arena)
                            Let elapsed_ns be string_to_integer(time_str)

                            Note: Find or create ProfileEntry for this function
                            Let entry be find_profile_entry(entries, func_name)
                            If entry is equal to 0:
                                Note: Create new entry
                                Set entry to arena_allocate(arena, PROFILE_ENTRY_SIZE, 8)
                                If entry is not equal to 0:
                                    memory_zero(entry, PROFILE_ENTRY_SIZE)
                                    memory_set_pointer(entry, 0, func_name)
                                    memory_set_integer(entry, 8, 0)
                                    memory_set_integer(entry, 24, 999999999)  Note: min starts high
                                    memory_set_integer(entry, 32, 0)           Note: max starts low
                                    arraylist_append(entries, entry)
                                    Let entry_count be memory_get_integer(data, 8)
                                    Set entry_count to entry_count plus 1
                                    memory_set_integer(data, 8, entry_count)
                                End If
                            End If

                            If entry is not equal to 0:
                                Note: Update call count
                                Let call_count be memory_get_integer(entry, 8)
                                Set call_count to call_count plus 1
                                memory_set_integer(entry, 8, call_count)

                                Note: Update total time
                                Let entry_total be memory_get_integer(entry, 16)
                                Set entry_total to entry_total plus elapsed_ns
                                memory_set_integer(entry, 16, entry_total)

                                Note: Update min time
                                Let entry_min be memory_get_integer(entry, 24)
                                If elapsed_ns is less than entry_min:
                                    memory_set_integer(entry, 24, elapsed_ns)
                                End If

                                Note: Update max time
                                Let entry_max be memory_get_integer(entry, 32)
                                If elapsed_ns is greater than entry_max:
                                    memory_set_integer(entry, 32, elapsed_ns)
                                End If

                                Set total_time to total_time plus elapsed_ns
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Set pos to line_end plus 1
    End While

    memory_set_integer(data, 16, total_time)

    Note: Compute averages and percentages for each entry
    Set entry_count to memory_get_integer(data, 8)
    Let idx be 0
    While idx is less than entry_count:
        Let entry_ptr be arraylist_get(entries, idx)
        If entry_ptr is not equal to 0:
            Set entry to memory_get_pointer(entry_ptr, 0)
            If entry is not equal to 0:
                Set call_count to memory_get_integer(entry, 8)
                Set entry_total to memory_get_integer(entry, 16)

                Note: Compute average
                If call_count is greater than 0:
                    Let avg be entry_total divided by call_count
                    memory_set_integer(entry, 40, avg)
                End If

                Note: Compute percentage (scaled by 100 for integer representation)
                If total_time is greater than 0:
                    Let percent_scaled be entry_total multiplied by 10000
                    Let percent be percent_scaled divided by total_time
                    memory_set_integer(entry, 48, percent)
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set idx to idx plus 1
    End While

    Return data
End Process

Process called "find_profile_entry" takes entries as Integer, func_name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Search the entries list for an existing ProfileEntry with the given function name
    Note: Returns pointer to the entry, or 0 if not found

    If entries is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If func_name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let count be arraylist_length(entries)
    Let idx be 0
    While idx is less than count:
        Let entry_ptr be arraylist_get(entries, idx)
        If entry_ptr is not equal to 0:
            Let entry be memory_get_pointer(entry_ptr, 0)
            If entry is not equal to 0:
                Let existing_name be memory_get_pointer(entry, 0)
                If existing_name is not equal to 0:
                    Let is_same be string_equals(existing_name, func_name)
                    If is_same is equal to 1:
                        Return entry
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set idx to idx plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Report Generation
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "generate_report" takes profile_data as Integer, arena as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Generate a formatted profiling report string from collected data
    Note: Returns pointer to report string, or 0 on failure

    If profile_data is equal to 0:
        Alert "[RUNAPROFILE ERROR] Cannot generate report: data is null"
        Return 0
    End If

    Let entries be memory_get_pointer(profile_data, 0)
    Let entry_count be memory_get_integer(profile_data, 8)
    Let total_time be memory_get_integer(profile_data, 16)

    Let report be string_duplicate("", arena)

    Note: Header
    Let header be string_concat(report, "==================================================\n")
    Set report to string_duplicate(header, arena)
    deallocate(header)

    Let title be string_concat(report, "[RUNAPROFILE] Performance Report\n")
    Set report to string_duplicate(title, arena)
    deallocate(title)

    Let sep be string_concat(report, "==================================================\n\n")
    Set report to string_duplicate(sep, arena)
    deallocate(sep)

    Note: Total execution time
    Let total_ms be total_time divided by 1000000
    Let total_line_pre be string_concat(report, "Total execution time: ")
    Let total_ms_str be integer_to_string(total_ms, arena)
    Let total_line be string_concat(total_line_pre, total_ms_str)
    deallocate(total_line_pre)
    Let total_line_post be string_concat(total_line, " ms\n\n")
    deallocate(total_line)
    Set report to string_duplicate(total_line_post, arena)
    deallocate(total_line_post)

    Note: Column headers
    Let col_header be string_concat(report, "Function                    Calls    Total(ms)    Avg(ns)    %\n")
    Set report to string_duplicate(col_header, arena)
    deallocate(col_header)

    Let col_sep be string_concat(report, "------------------------------------------------------------\n")
    Set report to string_duplicate(col_sep, arena)
    deallocate(col_sep)

    Note: Sort entries by total_time descending (identify hot functions)
    Note: Simple selection sort for stability
    Let sorted_indices be arena_allocate(arena, entry_count multiplied by 8, 8)
    If sorted_indices is not equal to 0:
        Note: Initialize indices
        Let init_idx be 0
        While init_idx is less than entry_count:
            memory_set_integer(sorted_indices, init_idx multiplied by 8, init_idx)
            Set init_idx to init_idx plus 1
        End While

        Note: Selection sort by total_time descending
        Let sort_i be 0
        While sort_i is less than entry_count:
            Let max_idx be sort_i
            Let max_time be 0
            Let entry_ptr be arraylist_get(entries, memory_get_integer(sorted_indices, sort_i multiplied by 8))
            If entry_ptr is not equal to 0:
                Let entry be memory_get_pointer(entry_ptr, 0)
                If entry is not equal to 0:
                    Set max_time to memory_get_integer(entry, 16)
                End If
            End If

            Let sort_j be sort_i plus 1
            While sort_j is less than entry_count:
                Let j_actual be memory_get_integer(sorted_indices, sort_j multiplied by 8)
                Let j_ptr be arraylist_get(entries, j_actual)
                If j_ptr is not equal to 0:
                    Let j_entry be memory_get_pointer(j_ptr, 0)
                    If j_entry is not equal to 0:
                        Let j_time be memory_get_integer(j_entry, 16)
                        If j_time is greater than max_time:
                            Set max_time to j_time
                            Set max_idx to sort_j
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
                Set sort_j to sort_j plus 1
            End While

            Note: Swap indices
            If max_idx is not equal to sort_i:
                Let temp_val be memory_get_integer(sorted_indices, sort_i multiplied by 8)
                Let swap_val be memory_get_integer(sorted_indices, max_idx multiplied by 8)
                memory_set_integer(sorted_indices, sort_i multiplied by 8, swap_val)
                memory_set_integer(sorted_indices, max_idx multiplied by 8, temp_val)
            End If

            Set sort_i to sort_i plus 1
        End While

        Note: Output sorted entries
        Let out_idx be 0
        While out_idx is less than entry_count:
            Let actual_idx be memory_get_integer(sorted_indices, out_idx multiplied by 8)
            Set entry_ptr to arraylist_get(entries, actual_idx)
            If entry_ptr is not equal to 0:
                Set entry to memory_get_pointer(entry_ptr, 0)
                If entry is not equal to 0:
                    Let func_name be memory_get_pointer(entry, 0)
                    Let call_count be memory_get_integer(entry, 8)
                    Let entry_total be memory_get_integer(entry, 16)
                    Let avg_ns be memory_get_integer(entry, 40)
                    Let percent be memory_get_integer(entry, 48)
                    Let entry_ms be entry_total divided by 1000000
                    Let percent_whole be percent divided by 100
                    Let percent_frac be percent minus percent_whole multiplied by 100

                    Let line_part be string_concat("  ", func_name)
                    Let line_p2 be string_concat(line_part, "  ")
                    deallocate(line_part)
                    Let calls_str be integer_to_string(call_count, arena)
                    Let line_p3 be string_concat(line_p2, calls_str)
                    deallocate(line_p2)
                    Let line_p4 be string_concat(line_p3, "  ")
                    deallocate(line_p3)
                    Let ms_str be integer_to_string(entry_ms, arena)
                    Let line_p5 be string_concat(line_p4, ms_str)
                    deallocate(line_p4)
                    Let line_p6 be string_concat(line_p5, "  ")
                    deallocate(line_p5)
                    Let avg_str be integer_to_string(avg_ns, arena)
                    Let line_p7 be string_concat(line_p6, avg_str)
                    deallocate(line_p6)
                    Let line_p8 be string_concat(line_p7, "  ")
                    deallocate(line_p7)
                    Let pct_str be integer_to_string(percent_whole, arena)
                    Let line_p9 be string_concat(line_p8, pct_str)
                    deallocate(line_p8)
                    Let line_p10 be string_concat(line_p9, "%\n")
                    deallocate(line_p9)

                    Let with_entry be string_concat(report, line_p10)
                    deallocate(line_p10)
                    Set report to string_duplicate(with_entry, arena)
                    deallocate(with_entry)
                End If
            End If
            Set out_idx to out_idx plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Note: Footer
    Let footer be string_concat(report, "\n==================================================\n")
    Set report to string_duplicate(footer, arena)
    deallocate(footer)

    Return report
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Hot Function Identification
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "identify_hot_functions" takes profile_data as Integer, top_n as Integer, arena as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Return a list of the top N functions by cumulative execution time
    Note: Returns pointer to ArrayList of ProfileEntry pointers (sorted by time descending)

    If profile_data is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let entries be memory_get_pointer(profile_data, 0)
    Let entry_count be memory_get_integer(profile_data, 8)

    If top_n is greater than entry_count:
        Set top_n to entry_count
    End If

    Let hot_list be arraylist_create(top_n, 8, arena)
    If hot_list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Find top N by iterating N times, each time picking the highest unselected
    Let selected be arena_allocate(arena, entry_count, 1)
    If selected is not equal to 0:
        memory_zero(selected, entry_count)

        Let pick be 0
        While pick is less than top_n:
            Let best_idx be -1
            Let best_time be -1

            Let scan_idx be 0
            While scan_idx is less than entry_count:
                Let is_selected be memory_get_byte(selected, scan_idx)
                If is_selected is equal to 0:
                    Let entry_ptr be arraylist_get(entries, scan_idx)
                    If entry_ptr is not equal to 0:
                        Let entry be memory_get_pointer(entry_ptr, 0)
                        If entry is not equal to 0:
                            Let entry_time be memory_get_integer(entry, 16)
                            If entry_time is greater than best_time:
                                Set best_time to entry_time
                                Set best_idx to scan_idx
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
                Set scan_idx to scan_idx plus 1
            End While

            If best_idx is greater than -1:
                memory_set_byte(selected, best_idx, 1)
                Let best_ptr be arraylist_get(entries, best_idx)
                If best_ptr is not equal to 0:
                    Let best_entry be memory_get_pointer(best_ptr, 0)
                    arraylist_append(hot_list, best_entry)
                End If
            End If

            Set pick to pick plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Return hot_list
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Top-Level Entry Point
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "run_profiler" takes argc as Integer, argv as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Main entry point for the RunaProfile tool
    Note: Instruments source, runs it, collects profile data, generates report
    Note: Returns exit code (0 = success, nonzero = failure)

    If argc is less than 2:
        Alert "[RUNAPROFILE] Usage: runa profile <source_file> [options]"
        Alert "[RUNAPROFILE] Options:"
        Alert "[RUNAPROFILE]   --iterations N   Run N iterations (default: 1)"
        Alert "[RUNAPROFILE]   --top N          Show top N hot functions (default: 10)"
        Alert "[RUNAPROFILE]   --output <file>  Write report to file"
        Alert "[RUNAPROFILE]   --verbose        Enable verbose output"
        Return PROFILE_TOOL_INVALID_ARGS
    End If

    Let arena be arena_create(262144)
    If arena is equal to 0:
        Alert "[RUNAPROFILE ERROR] Failed to create arena"
        Return PROFILE_TOOL_FAILURE
    End If

    Let source_path be 0
    Let iterations be PROFILE_DEFAULT_ITERATIONS
    Let top_n be 10
    Let output_file be 0
    Let is_verbose be 0
    Let ptr_size be 8
    Let i be 1

    While i is less than argc:
        Let arg_offset be i multiplied by ptr_size
        Let arg_ptr be argv plus arg_offset
        Let arg be memory_get_pointer(arg_ptr, 0)

        If arg is not equal to 0:
            Let is_iter be string_equals(arg, "--iterations")
            Let is_top be string_equals(arg, "--top")
            Let is_output be string_equals(arg, "--output")
            Let is_verbose_flag be string_equals(arg, "--verbose")
            Let handled be 0
            If is_iter is equal to 1:
                Set handled to 1
                Set i to i plus 1
                If i is less than argc:
                    Let next_offset be i multiplied by ptr_size
                    Let next_ptr be argv plus next_offset
                    Let iter_str be memory_get_pointer(next_ptr, 0)
                    If iter_str is not equal to 0:
                        Set iterations to string_to_integer(iter_str)
                        If iterations is less than 1:
                            Set iterations to 1
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
            If handled is equal to 0:
                If is_top is equal to 1:
                    Set handled to 1
                    Set i to i plus 1
                    If i is less than argc:
                        Let next_offset2 be i multiplied by ptr_size
                        Let next_ptr2 be argv plus next_offset2
                        Let top_str be memory_get_pointer(next_ptr2, 0)
                        If top_str is not equal to 0:
                            Set top_n to string_to_integer(top_str)
                            If top_n is less than 1:
                                Set top_n to 10
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
            If handled is equal to 0:
                If is_output is equal to 1:
                    Set handled to 1
                    Set i to i plus 1
                    If i is less than argc:
                        Let next_offset3 be i multiplied by ptr_size
                        Let next_ptr3 be argv plus next_offset3
                        Set output_file to memory_get_pointer(next_ptr3, 0)
                    End If
                End If
            End If
            If handled is equal to 0:
                If is_verbose_flag is equal to 1:
                    Set is_verbose to 1
                    Set handled to 1
                End If
            End If
            If handled is equal to 0:
                Set source_path to arg
            End If
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    If source_path is equal to 0:
        Alert "[RUNAPROFILE ERROR] No source file specified"
        arena_destroy(arena)
        Return PROFILE_TOOL_INVALID_ARGS
    End If

    Note: Read source file
    Let source be runtime_read_file(source_path)
    If source is equal to 0:
        Let err_msg be string_concat("[RUNAPROFILE ERROR] Cannot read: ", source_path)
        Alert err_msg
        deallocate(err_msg)
        arena_destroy(arena)
        Return PROFILE_TOOL_FAILURE
    End If

    Display "[RUNAPROFILE] Instrumenting: "
    Display source_path

    Note: Instrument the source
    Let instrumented be instrument_source(source, arena)
    deallocate(source)
    If instrumented is equal to 0:
        Alert "[RUNAPROFILE ERROR] Instrumentation failed"
        arena_destroy(arena)
        Return PROFILE_TOOL_FAILURE
    End If

    Note: Write instrumented source to a temporary file
    Let inst_path be string_concat(source_path, ".profiled.runa")
    Let inst_len be string_length(instrumented)
    Let write_result be runtime_write_file(inst_path, instrumented, inst_len)

    If write_result is not equal to 0:
        Alert "[RUNAPROFILE ERROR] Failed to write instrumented source"
        deallocate(inst_path)
        arena_destroy(arena)
        Return PROFILE_TOOL_FAILURE
    End If

    Display "[RUNAPROFILE] Running "
    Display iterations
    Display " iteration(s)..."

    Note: Compile and execute the instrumented source
    Note: Capture stdout as profile output
    Let profile_output be compile_and_run(inst_path, arena)
    deallocate(inst_path)

    If profile_output is equal to 0:
        Alert "[RUNAPROFILE ERROR] Execution failed"
        arena_destroy(arena)
        Return PROFILE_TOOL_FAILURE
    End If

    Note: Collect profiling data
    Let profile_data be collect_profile_data(profile_output, arena)
    If profile_data is equal to 0:
        Alert "[RUNAPROFILE ERROR] Data collection failed"
        arena_destroy(arena)
        Return PROFILE_TOOL_FAILURE
    End If

    memory_set_integer(profile_data, 32, iterations)

    Note: Generate report
    Let report be generate_report(profile_data, arena)
    If report is not equal to 0:
        Note: Display or write report
        If output_file is not equal to 0:
            Let report_len be string_length(report)
            Let report_write be runtime_write_file(output_file, report, report_len)
            Display "[RUNAPROFILE] Report written to: "
            Display output_file
        Otherwise:
            Display report
        End If
    End If

    Note: Identify and display hot functions
    Let hot_functions be identify_hot_functions(profile_data, top_n, arena)
    If hot_functions is not equal to 0:
        Display "[RUNAPROFILE] Top "
        Display top_n
        Display " hot functions identified"
    End If

    arena_destroy(arena)
    Return PROFILE_TOOL_SUCCESS
End Process
